A man has died after a car left the road and hit a tree in Suffolk.Police were called to reports of a single-vehicle collision on Halesworth Road in Reydon, near Southwold, at 15:30 BST on Tuesday.The driver of a black Vauxhall Zafira, a man in his 60s, was taken to Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital by air ambulance before he died. His two passengers, a man and a woman both in their 30s, were uninjured. 
The East Anglian Air Ambulance helicopter was in attendance along with a community first responder, rapid response vehicle and an ambulance as well as Suffolk Fire and Rescue Service crews before the road reopened at 18:10.Suffolk Police is urging any witnesses or anyone with dashcam footage to come forward.Anyone with information can contact the Serious Collision Investigation Team on 101 quoting 37/19521/24.
